OL,3,CSpike in vandalism prompts call to
OL,4,Cprotect historic sites
OL,6,FEarlier this year new interpretation
OL,7,Fsignage was damaged and the grass torn
OL,8,Fup after intruders broke into the site
OL,9,Fand used it as a bike track. In a
OL,10,Fseparate act of vandalism, windows to
OL,11,Fthe abbey's undercroft were smashed
OL,12,Fand panels from an unopened exhibition
OL,13,Fwere destroyed.
OL,15,FAt Blaenavon Ironworks, a UNESCO World
OL,16,FHeritage Site, vandals forced the
OL,17,Fclosure of the Cast House after an
OL,18,Faudiovisual display was destroyed and
OL,19,Fbricks were thrown from the top of a
OL,20,Ftower.
