OL,3,CSpike in vandalism prompts call to
OL,4,Cprotect historic sites
OL,6,FIn emergencies, the public is advised
OL,7,Fto call 999 and reference 'Operation
OL,8,FHeritage Cymru.' Non-emergency reports
OL,9,Fcan be made via 101 using the same
OL,10,Fphrase. Anonymous tips can be
OL,11,Fsubmitted to Crimestoppers.
OL,13,FDamage involving scheduled monuments
OL,14,Fcan also be reported directly to Cadw,
OL,15,Fwhile listed building issues should be
OL,16,Fflagged with local authority
OL,17,Fconservation officers. Residents are
OL,18,Falso encouraged to join local Heritage
OL,19,FWatch schemes to support efforts to
OL,20,Fsafeguard historic sites.
